# Extend vs Create Drop-ins

## Extend When

- Adding features to existing drop-ins (Cart, Checkout, PDP, etc.)
- Use **slots** to inject custom UI into containers
- Use **events** to react to drop-in lifecycle
- Extend GraphQL fragments via `overrideGQLOperations` in build.mjs
- Add custom data via model transformers in initializers

## Create When

- Building entirely new commerce functionality not covered by B2C/B2B drop-ins
- Use **dropin-template**: https://github.com/adobe-commerce/dropin-template
- Follow Elsie CLI: `npx elsie generate config|component|container|api`
- Structure: `src/{api,components,containers,render}/`

## Key References

- Extending: https://experienceleague.adobe.com/developer/commerce/storefront/dropins/all/extending/
- Creating: https://experienceleague.adobe.com/developer/commerce/storefront/dropins/all/creating/
